name.html: Salesforce Park Movie Nights: November  15 - Say Anything

description.text:
Enjoy FREE movies in Salesforce Park this November under the stars with four fan favorites at the amphitheater! 
Pre-registration through Eventbrite is required. The amphitheater lawn will open at 4:30 pm for those who have pre-registered. Be prepared to show RSVP confirmation. Anyone who has not pre-registered will only be allowed in on a first-come, first-served basis 5 minutes before the movie starts. 
Attendees are welcome to bring personal food and non-alcoholic beverages, and chairs that sit at ground level. Chairs that sit above two-inches from the ground, tents, wheeled coolers, or outside alcoholic beverages are NOT allowed. Please be mindful of the shared space while claiming your spot. Strollers must be collapsed during the film. Capacity is limited. Pre-registration check-in will close 10 minutes before movie starts. 
Movie Night Schedule: 
Nov 1: The Brave Little Toaster (G, 90 mins) @ 6:30pm (later start time)
Nov 8: Honey, I Shrunk the Kids (PG, 101 mins) @ 6pm
Nov 15: Say Anything (PG-13, 101 mins) @ 6pm
Nov 22: Spaceballs (PG, 96 mins) @ 6pm 

If you have any questions about the event, please contact: Salesforceparkevents@brvcorp.com

description.text:
Take your next dinner party to the next level. Under the guidance of a professional Old Liquors ambassador, you will enjoy 5 ultra-rare vintage cognacs.
An Old Liquors Ambassador will come to your home and guide you and your guests through the nuances of incredibly rare spirits. The Brand Ambassador will mix ‘The Summit’, a cognac cocktail to start of the evening and bring 5 ultra-rare cognacs for you to enjoy along with the required glassware.
You and your distinguished guests will be tasting
The Summit cognac cocktail for guest to enjoy during the event introduction.5 rare exceptional vintage cognacs including:
o Ultra-Premium Remy Martin Louis XIII cognac from the 1990so Croizet Swinging sixties cognac, vintage 1963, aged over 50 yearso 1914 Restaurant Maxim’s Paris WWI Ladies vintage cognac, aged over 50 yearso Phillip de Castaigne Belle Époque era Folle Blanche vintage cognac 1893o Pre-Phylloxera era Napoleon vintage cognac 1811
An Old Liquors Tasting Event is as much an emotional journey as it is a sensory delight that evokes pure bliss. A tasting is something you have to share with the one who is beside you. It allows you to share experiences with friends that go beyond words. Feelings that are expressed in a look and a smile as the exceptional aura of rare cognac emerges from the glass and fills the room.Tasting exceptional spirits takes you back in time and unlocks hidden memories of tastes. When an age-old bottle is opened, it reveals a myriad of scents captured in a bouquet of myrrh, honey, dried roses, plum, honeysuckle, cigar box, leather, figs, and passion fruit. This is the magic of time captured in a bottle.  Each bottle that is opened is the lifetime achievement of a cellar master, an art and savoir-faire carefully captured in glass. It is a tribute to the work from the terroir, by the people, and across time.The Old Liquors Brand ambassador helps to give the senses a voice and share your feelings. You will receive expert instruction on how best to slowly take the time to let the waves of aromas and tastes fill your pallet. You learn to discover what is hidden in the depths of age the old Eaux-de-Vie. Experience what you thought you would never encounter. You and your guest develop your noses and palates thanks to these sharing moments. 

Practical information:

The tasting is meant to be a compliment to an existing event.
Booking minimally 30 days in advance.
Number of guests: minimum 8* to maximum 20.
Targeted audience: cognac lovers, beginners or experts, company seminars
Driving distance: Venues targeted are within a 45-mile radius of the int. airport.
Time schedule: The date must be fixed upon 30 days ahead of time.
Glassware and cognac along with serving trays and cocktails will be provided.
All participants must be over the age of 21.
Languages available: English (please contact us for other languages)
Tasting gift sets including 3 rare vintage cognacs can be obtained separately from the Old Liquors Ambassador, a list will be provided after booking.
Cost: $500 per person, minimum of 8* persons
Cancellation: Orders are considered confirmed upon reception of payment. All cancellations made more than 30 days prior to the reservation will be fully reimbursed, half of the payment will be reimbursed for cancellations within 4 weeks of the reservation date and no reimbursement will be possible for cancellations less than one week before the date of the class.

*small groups are welcome but will be charged a minimum flat rate equal to the price of 8 guests.

description.text:
>> Just 200 Tickets Per Show 
HellaFunny and Funcheap are taking over the Neck of the Woods and turning it into a secret pop-up comedy club for one weekend. Come enjoy some big laughs with some of SF's best comedians. Comedians from this show have been seen on NBC, ABC, Viceland, MTV, Netflix, Cobb's, SF Sketchfest, Clusterfest and more. General Admission tickets at the door are $10, but you'll get on our exclusive guest list here.
> Donations appreciated  If you have the means, help support the show 
November 2019 Lineup
Friday 11/15Clay Newman-San Francisco Comedy Competition finalist, SF Punchline Emily Ward-SF PunchlineTony Sparks- Godfather of Bay Area Comedy
Saturday 11/16Jalisa Robinson-SF SketchfestPaco Romane-Comedy CentralDaniel Dugar-Opened for D.L. Hughley, Cedric the Entertainer
About the Producers:
HellaFunny Comedy Night is produced by Bay Area Comedy Collective #HellaFunny. #HellaFunny produces comedy shows throughout the Bay Area 7 nights a week in venues including Cobbs, Punchline, the Great Star Theater, Milk Bar, Starline Social Club, Slate Bar, Eastside West, the Neck of the Woods and more. Comedian and CEO of #HellaFunny, Stroy Moyd, is 10-year veteran and has been seen on Tech Crunch, Vox, Complex News, Good Morning America, NBC Nightly News and Viceland.
Frequently Asked Questions:

Has anyone famous ever performed at a HellaFunny Show? - Yes indeed! HellaFunny has been able to attract talent of national headliners such as Hannibal Buress (Broad City), Mike E. Winfield (The Office), Jermaine Fowler (ABC's Superior Donuts), The Lucas Brothers (Netflix Special "On Drugs") and more!
What time should I arrive? - We suggest everyone arrive 30 minutes prior to showtime!
Do you serve food? - The Neck of the Woods does not serve food. However, there are plenty of restaurants near by and you can bring your food in and watch the show no problem!
Is there an age limit? - Yes, 21 and up.
How's parking? - Little street parking is available. However, we suggest using Lyft or another ridesharing app.
Is there a dress code? - Dress to impress!

Are you having trouble controlling the way you eat? Food Addicts in Recovery Anonymous (FA) is a free Twelve Step recovery program for anyone suffering from food obsession, overeating, under-eating or bulimia. Meetings are held Saturday at St. Marks Church/Urban Life Center, 1031 Franklin St. in San Francisco at 9:00am. For more information or a list of additional meetings throughout the U.S. and the world, call 781-932-6300 or visit: www.foodaddicts.org.

ABOUT FOOD ADDICTS IN RECOVERY ANONYMOUS



 Food Addicts in Recovery Anonymous is a 12 Step fellowship based on the principles of Alcoholics Anonymous (AA). FA is a tax-exempt, non-profit Twelve Step program that helps people of all ages who have issues with food. There are no dues or fees for members. Anyone, from any walk of life, who seeks recovery from their problems with food, is welcome. 

The following meeting is held in San Francisco every week:



Saturday - 9:00am

name.html: Luaupalooza at Trailblazer Tavern

description.text:
Every Saturday morning and afternoon a festive, island-inspired brunch combining classic breakfast dishes alongside nostalgic Hawaiian comfort foods complemented by live music and curated playlists to fully immerse guests in the tropical dining experience.
Island-inspired dish highlights include: 

Shrimp Toast on Japanese white bread with sweet shrimp and black sesame
S.P.A.M. Musubi with Mochi-Crusted Smoked Pork Arabiki Meatloaf
Loco Moco eggs any style with shiitake gravy, available with a beef or beet patty
Pipikaula Hash with Hawaiian beef “jerky”, Yukon potatoes, market vegetables and eggs any style 
Housemade S.P.A.M. Benedict served on an English muffin with Hollandaise and breakfast potatoes
Mochi Pancakes with P.O.G. coulis, macadamia praline and coconut whipped cream
French Toast with salted peanut brittle, brûléed banana, and 5 spice maple syrup

Tropical beverages will transport guests to the islands; highlights include:

Lilikoi Margarita blended with Espolon Blanco, Combier, lilikoi, lime and finished with a li hing mui rim 
Myna Bird Piña Colada blended with Don Q Cristal, pineapple and coconut cream 
P.O.G. Mimosa with prosecco, passion fruit, orange and guava puree

description.text:
Are you having trouble controlling the way you eat? Food Addicts in Recovery Anonymous (FA) is a free Twelve Step recovery program for anyone suffering from food obsession, overeating, under-eating or bulimia. Meetings are held Saturday at St. Marks Church/Urban Life Center, 1031 Franklin St. in San Francisco at 9:00am. For more information or a list of additional meetings throughout the U.S. and the world, call 781-932-6300 or visit: www.foodaddicts.org.

ABOUT FOOD ADDICTS IN RECOVERY ANONYMOUS



 Food Addicts in Recovery Anonymous is a 12 Step fellowship based on the principles of Alcoholics Anonymous (AA). FA is a tax-exempt, non-profit Twelve Step program that helps people of all ages who have issues with food. There are no dues or fees for members. Anyone, from any walk of life, who seeks recovery from their problems with food, is welcome. 

The following meeting is held in San Francisco every week:



Sunday - 8:00 am
California Pacific Medical Center - First Level, Enright Room
2333 Buchanan St., San Francisco, CA 94115

name.html: Neomodern Coworking Space for Photographers (+ Print Your Pics!)

description.text:
Welcome to Neomodern! Your very own photography hub and workspace!
Tired of working on your photos alone? Need an excuse to leave your apartment? Do you sometimes need just a touch of outside advice or guidance from pros? Come work at the Neomodern Flagship Store. You're not only sitting around other photographers and experts at Photoshop and Lightroom, but you can get your creative juices flowing being surrounded by great photos (including masterworks from Ansel Adams, Cartier-Bresson, and others). And unlike any other coworking space, if you want, you can leave with something extra. 
If you'd like to print (or frame) some of your photographs, you can simply tell us when you're visiting, or upload them here and we will work on them with you. You can have your very own framed piece in under 30 minutes! You won't pay for the coworking space but only the regular costs for the prints or framed projects. As an introduction to Neomodern, we're also giving you 10% off all your projects. Just let our team know that you found us on Eventbrite! 
We're inviting local photographers and creatives to use our gallery as a coworking space every Monday, Wednesday, and Friday between 1pm to 5pm. We've got free wifi, café tables, a comfy couch for lounging… and with Starbucks across the street, all the coffee you can drink, and a friendly and knowledgable staff of pro photographers.We’re located smack-dab in the middle of Cow Hollow, with yoga, food and libations abound.  We opened our Flagship Store in June 2017—and we couldn't be more stoked to share it with you. Stop in to chill with us, commune with like-minded creatives, and even work on some of your stunning captures together!Please RSVP to reserve a spot. We kindly ask that you remove your RSVP if you don't plan to come so that somebody else can nab your space. We're a store in a busy part of town, so we can't always guarantee that we'll have a seat for you, so you're free to drop by, but it's always smarter to plan ahead.

As an added bonus for spreading some Neomodern love, we'll gift you with a free print:

Take a selfie at Neomodern inside our incredible gallery
Follow @neomodernsf
Tag @neomodernsf on Instagram Instagram (make sure your profile is public)

We'll DM you a personal code (for a free print) which you can apply at check out.

name.html: A Cappella Workshop and Open Rehearsal  with Keeva A Cappella

description.text:
Miss singing regularly? Looking for a low-pressure, no cost singing opportunity? Come warm up your vocal chords and sing with Keeva A Cappella at an evening workshop! 
WHAT YOU GET?

Fun, free evening of singing 
Experience singing in a group
Low pressure chance to practice a cappella
Feel-good experience that is cheaper than therapy!

WHAT TO EXPECT?

Meet Keeva, a long time SF a cappella group
Learn and sing exciting vocal exercises
Learn songs from around the world including "Akhekho Ofana No Jesu", "Sto Mi e Milo", and "Dancing on My Own"
The workshop acts as an informal, low pressure, audition since we are always looking for new members.

FAQs
Do I need a cappella experience to attend?
Any and all singers are welcome to attend regardless of experience level or skill. If you sing karaoke, musical theater, choir, glee club, or college a cappella, you are over-qualified.  Any experience is good experience! We will be teaching music by call and response so no music reading ability is needed to participate and have fun. We will have sheet music for everyone too if that is more your style!  
What are my transportation/parking options for getting to and from the event?
Counterpulse theater is in the heart of San Francisco and has very convenient public transit options including Bart and Muni.  There are also street parking and garages nearby.
What can I bring into the event?
Bring yourselves but please no pets or food!
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
Please email keevasf@gmail.com with any questions

name.text: Smash Bros Mondays!
name.html: Smash Bros Mondays!

description.text:
Grab a drink, grab some food and get ready to play! The Super Trashed Bros. are hosting a weekly Super Smash Bros Ultimate night at the neighborhood arcade/craft beer bar/restaurant Detour SF! 
Our gaming nights have a set of conditions called "The JaRules."If you are playing, and this condition occurs, you have to take a sip of your drink! For instance, if you lose a stock in Super Smash Bros, you take a sip! If you lose a stock by accident, take two sips! If you lose a stock being hit by a Final Smash, take three sips! If you call them anything other than "JaRules"—it doesn't matter if you're drinking water or a delicious craft beer—take a sip! It's all about managing your sips to the gameplay and it's harder than it looks. 
Sometimes it'll be a casual, friendly freeplay, other times it's a knock down, drag out tournament. Check our Facebook for format updates. Sign-ups open around 7 p.m., and run throughout the event. Prizes for winner and runner-up, as well as most enthusiastic player or crowd member!
ABOUT US: Super Trashed Bros. brings together comedy, video games, and alcohol. Join our hosts, as well as assorted merrymakers, as they cook up amazing video-game drinking competitions. It's e-sports gone mild! It's low-stakes gaming and high-end drinks! It’s like a house party with funnier friends!ABOUT VENUE: The Detour brings to you a re-imagined version of the neighborhood arcade and interactive space. Quality drinks, comforting bites, a curated mix of games -- both classic and new -- all come together in a playfully warm industrial space. The Detour offers a wide variety of experiences under one roof. The Detour will be defined as San Francisco’s neighborhood all-in-one stop for drinks, food and fun for ALL AGES.

description.text:
Blackthorn Tavern's Monday night trivia night was named one of San Francisco's 8 best trivia nights by Thrillist (https://www.thrillist.com/drink/san-francisco/sf-pub-quiz-trivia-night-bars).
To see more awesome Urban Adventure Club events, please visit us at: https://urbanadventureclub.com/Events
Quizmaster Peter Malone asks 6 rounds of questions (which progressively gets more challenging) ranging from entertainment to sports to history to geography. He also includes a picture round and a "Name That Artist/Group" music round.
We usually get a decent sized team for this trivia. Beginners are welcome. You don't have to be good at trivia, you just need to have a good time!
Arrive early for a seat at the table because the bar gets crowded. Since we do pretty well at this trivia, we usually have drink tickets to buy free beer with!

How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
We will meet at 8pm to get seats, save a table & socialize. Text Kimble at 415-310-5694 if you can't find the group.

description.text:
“Accessibility is an outcome. Inclusive design is a process.”— Derek Featherstone
Join product designers from Google, Remind, Splunk, and Thumbtack for an evening of thought-provoking talks about designing with empathy. The second installment of the Remind Assembly Series, Designing for Inclusion explores different questions of diversity, equity, and inclusion at the intersection of product design and user experience. Drinks and light food will be provided. This event is free, open to the public, and wheelchair-accessible; talks will include live closed captions, and the event will be streamed and recorded for anyone who can't join us in San Francisco. We ask all participants to comply with our code of conduct.

name.text: San Francisco Homelessness Datathon - Volunteering Opportunities for November 12th and 19th
name.html: San Francisco Homelessness Datathon - Volunteering Opportunities for November 12th and 19th

description.text:
We, Sheltertech, are creating an online directory resource (think Yelp!) to help the underserved community in San Francisco gaining information on accessible basic amenities (i.e food, shelter, shower). One of the regular public events/workshops we held is Datathon, which is an opportunity for you to work side-by-side with community representatives - people who are currently or have previously been homeless - to verify and vet information and make sure the 1000+ services in our system is correct.
As a non-profit, we rely heavily on the power of our community (that is you!) and hence we would like to invite people like you to join our cause in making a lasting impact to help the underserved community in San Francisco! We have welcomed volunteers from a wide range of experience & passion for our cause! So, whether you are simply looking to meet new people or to learn more about the struggles faced by the homeless community, this event would be a great experience for you!
-----
What will you do at this "Datathon"?
During this Datathon, you'll work side-by-side with Community Representatives -- people who are currently or have previously been homeless -- to verify information and make sure the 1000+ services in our system are correct. This is a great way to learn about some of the struggles faced by people experiencing homelessness and have an immediate impact in helping them. Plus you get to meet new like-minded people (fellow volunteers and sheltertech team members) and there will be free food and drinks!
----
Operational details:
When entering the building, please notify the front desk security guard that you are heading to the 17th floor WeWork so that you may proceed. Any questions and concerns please contact Raphaël @ 817-525-5752.
Snack and beverages will be provided for volunteers :-)
No special skills required, just basic internet browsing and typing!
Please bring your own laptop

---
Program
5:45pm - 6:00pm Social event & mingle
6:00pm - 8:00pm Data vetting & networking
-----

name.html: Peace, Serenity, and Joy for New Parents *Free Webinar*

description.text:
How much would you love to receive help and support in navigating the first year with your first-born or second-born child and all the challenges, uncertainty, stress, anxiety, and mixed emotions that come with it? As a parent with two young children, I remember those early days being especially emotionally and physically challenging, when merely brushing my hair, showering, eating food that was still warm, or going to the bathroom in peace felt like major accomplishments.
Support from a certified personal coach who was completely unbiased, open, compassionate, and there for the sole purpose of holding space for me to share, explore, and process, while listening attentively, able to empathize with what I was going through, and validating what I was experiencing would have been wonderful. If this applies to you, this "coachinar" is a must for you!  
During the interactive session, conducted via Zoom (yes, you can be in your pajamas), you will:


Explore what you want most (e.g. reconnecting with yourself, carving out “me time,” adjusting to changing dynamics with your partner, honoring values that have been neglected, navigating family expectations, determining and living into who you want to be as a parent, quieting worry and self-doubt, debating about returning to work, etc.)




Recognize the values that are honored in that place or places




Create a clearer vision of what that looks like within your role as a parent




Explore what is most resonant for you in that place or places




Identify ways to get closer to making that vision a reality, and thereby experiencing more joy and less stress as a parent




Identify and commit to steps you will take in that direction


Enjoy a sense of community among others who can relate to what you're experiencing




Complete the webinar with action items that, put into practice, will make positive differences immediately


Upon completion of the webinar, you will have the option to schedule a complimentary one-on-one 30-minute phone or video conversation to further discuss your challenges and desires, and explore ways to bridge the gap between your current situation and how you want it to be.
What are you waiting for? Reserve your spot now to join for a dynamic and impactful session! Space is limited.
 
How can I contact the organizer with any questions?
lisha@coachlisha.com

name.text: Peak Design: Coworking for Creatives
name.html: Peak Design: Coworking for Creatives

description.text:
Tired of editing alone? Wanna get creative juices flowing? Need an excuse to put on pants and leave your apartment? Come work at the Peak Design Flagship Store.
We're inviting local photographers and creatives to use our retail store as a coworking space every Weds between 1pm and 5:30pm. We know a retail store isn't your typical work spot but we're different. We've got free wifi, a big wooden table with power outlets, a comfy couch for lounging, all the coffee you can drink, a clean bathroom, a friendly and knowledgable staff of pro photographers, and we're located smack-dab in the middle of Hayes Valley, with food and libations abound.

Please RSVP to reserve a spot. We kindly ask that you remove your RSVP if you don't plan to come so that somebody else can nab your space. We're a store in a busy part of town, so we can't always guarantee that we'll have space for you, so please plan accordingly.
About Us:
We're Peak Design, an SF-based product design company. We specialize in carry goods: products that help you carry, organize, and manage your things. We make gear for photographers, creatives, travelers, commuters, and everyone in-between. We're proud members of 1% For The Planet, and we created Giveashot.org to connect creatives with environmental nonprofits in need of content.
We opened our Flagship Store in December 2017—it's our very first physical space—and we couldn't be more stoked to share it with you. Come say hey.
